	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=2117&mid=106668816285424>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=2117&mid=106668816285424>Don't bother</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=2117&mid=106668816285424#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Oct 20th 6:23 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=199333><span id= >RUSHSF</span></a><br><span id=notbold>37 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.71]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I always wanted a mana robe and finally got one, I also have my epic. It gets very tiresome chaing the robe and recasting epic. The graphic is cool and all but the stats suck and the chest piece is really not a slot I want to give up. I used it for 4 days and sold it. I am a lvl 65 wizard with several ft items, my top aa familiar and I have 152 aa. I never run out of mana either in a group or on a raid. If your standing there chaining this and recasting epic you would better serve your friends by doing some dmage instead. Someone might say but hey man what if you just got a rez and need some mana to help the raid..blah blah blah. I say you get rez on raid and first thing is cast epic (rune has mana regen) use mod rod, click your AA familiar to get them mana pool and mana regen going some more and finally hit both your harvests. If your lucky some enchanter on the raid will have tgb C5 on ya by then and your almost at fm and ready to get some revenge.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
